full_text: Due to ongoing unfavorable weather at the launch and recovery sites, now targeting Thursday, June 20 for Falcon 9’s launch of the @SES_Satellites ASTRA 1P mission from Florida. The ~3-hour window opens at 5:35 p.m. ET → https://t.co/bJFjLCiTbK
Falcon 9 delivers 20 @Starlink  satellites to orbit from California https://t.co/cIxiifeAGj
Falcon 9’s first stage has landed on Of Course I Still Love You droneship https://t.co/oftsMhP728
Watch Falcon 9 launch 20 @Starlink satellites to orbit from California, including 13 with Direct to Cell capabilities https://t.co/NXEjHN5Cok

All systems are looking good, weather is 90% favorable, and propellant load is about to begin for today’s launch of 20 @Starlink satellites from California → https://t.co/DngkHY8cZI https://t.co/QyWf4nzSM5
Standing down from today's launch of the @SES_Satellites ASTRA 1P mission due to unfavorable weather conditions in Florida. Now targeting tomorrow, June 19 for liftoff → https://t.co/bJFjLCiTbK

@SES_Satellites ASTRA 1P is our 12th dedicated mission with @SES_Satellites, having first launched SES-8 in 2013, followed by the first reflight of Falcon 9 during SES-10, and most recently, the third O3B mPOWER mission last year https://t.co/YS6OjUrTNf
Watch Falcon 9 launch the @SES_Satellites ASTRA 1P mission to orbit https://t.co/nTIXB5J053
Propellant load is underway for Falcon 9’s launch of the @SES_Satellites ASTRA 1P mission from Florida. Teams are continuing to monitor winds → https://t.co/bJFjLCiTbK

Falcon 9 is vertical at SLC-40 ahead of today’s launch of the @SES_Satellites ASTRA 1P mission, which is now targeted for 8:23 p.m. ET due to elevated winds at the launch site. Teams are continuing to monitor weather, which is currently 55% favorable https://t.co/82VPb3VFml
